Set WSL 2 as your default version
Open PowerShell and run this command to set WSL 2 as the default version.

Powershell
1
wsl --set-default-version 2
Common Errors

1. The term wsl is not recognized as the name of the cmdlet ....
This only happens if you have missed one of the previous steps. Or if you still need to install some of the Windows Updates.

Please check for Windows updates and re-do the previous steps again to fix this issue.
